      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>A barrier of light, colored as you choose, springs into existence. You can form the wall into a vertical or horizontal plane, but each 10-foot square must join another. The light level within 5 feet of the wall increases to normal light. Within an additional 5 feet, the light increases one step, up to normal light. When you concentrate on the spell, you can change the light&rsquo;s color.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can have only one </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">glowing wall </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">spell active at a time. If you cast this spell while another casting is still in effect, the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">previous casting is dispelled. A </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">glowing wall </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">somehow made permanent doesn&rsquo;t count against this limit.</span> </p>"
